keyFacts: A proffer interview was conducted on August 28, 2019, as part of an investigation related to the Epstein case.
The interview took place at the U.S. Attorney's Office for the Southern District of New York.
Multiple law enforcement agencies were represented, including the FBI, a Task Force Officer Detective, and the Office of Inspector General.
The document is an FBI FD-302 form dated September 23, 2019, which records the substance of the proffer interview.
The document states it contains neither recommendations nor conclusions of the FBI and is not to be distributed outside the receiving agency.
